<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-8446] Kafka Streams restoration crashes with NPE when the record value is null</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8446</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;To add more context here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a NPE will be triggered in &lt;b&gt;RecordConverters#ByteBuffer.allocate(8 + rawValue.length)&lt;/b&gt;&#160;if the raw value with record is null. A scenario you could reproduce is like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Having a source KTable (timestampedKeyValueStore) reads in tombstone&#160;records where the value field is null. Note that you need to turn off stream level cache, otherwise the null value will not be forwarded.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Shutdown the application, and clear local state stores.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Restart the application before changelog topic starts compaction. If we are &quot;lucky&quot;, the tombstone record will trigger null pointer exception during restoration when we try to extract raw value length.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
